e<\/a><\/div><\/figure>\n<\/figure>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<p>The facade and the church&#x2019;s interior have beautiful details, but the main draw of this building is its huge exterior wall of azulejos tiles that tell the story of the Carmelite order.<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"block-link block-link--tip \">\n                <div class=\"block-link__container\">\n\n                    <div class=\"salt-icon__container\">\n                        <span class=\"salt-icon salt-icon--tip\"><\/span>\n                        <svg class=\"icon icon-round-shape\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-round-shape\"><\/use><\/svg>\n                    <\/div>\n\n                    <p>Portugal has more to offer! Like <a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/portugal\/monsanto-rock-village\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Monsanto, the village built on rocks.<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n                <\/div>\n            <\/div>\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/23105311\/porto-portugal-Igreja-do-Carmo.jpg\" alt=\"porto portugal Igreja do Carmo\"><\/noscript><img width=\"450\" height=\"326\" alt=\"porto portugal Igreja do Carmo\" class=\"wp-image-48355 lazypreload\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/23105311\/porto-portugal-Igreja-do-Carmo.jpg 1920w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/23105311\/porto-portugal-Igreja-do-Carmo-300x218.jpg 300w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/23105311\/porto-portugal-Igreja-do-Carmo-600x435.jpg 600w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/23105311\/porto-portugal-Igreja-do-Carmo-800x580.jpg 800w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-cont